\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
\par Now it came to pass in the thirtieth year, in the fourth month, on the fifth day of the month, that I was in the midst of the captivity by the river of Chobar; and the heavens were opened, and I saw visions of God.}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 On the fifth day of the month; this was the fifth year of the captivity of king Joakim.}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the word of the Lord came to Jezekiel the priest, the son of Buzi, in the land of the Chaldeans, by the river of Chobar; and the hand of the Lord was upon me.}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And I looked, and, behold, 
a sweeping wind came from the north, and a great cloud on it, and brightness round about it, and gleaming fire, and in the midst of it as it were the appearance of amber in the midst of the fire, and brightness in it.}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And in the midst as it were the likeness of four living creatures. And this was their appearance; the likeness of a man was upon them.}{\insrsid8136756  6 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And each one four faces, and each one four wings.}{\insrsid8136756  7 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And their legs were straight; and their feet were winged, and sparks, like gleaming brass, and their wings were light.}{\insrsid8136756  8 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the hand of a man was under their wings on their four sides.}{\insrsid8136756  9 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the faces of them four turned not when they went; they went everyone straight forward.}{\insrsid8136756 
 10 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the likeness of their faces was the face of a man, and the face of a lion on the right of the four; and the face of a calf on the left of the four; and the face of an eagle to the four.}{\insrsid8136756  11 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the four had their wings spread out above; each one two joined to one another, and two covered their bodies.}{\insrsid8136756  12 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And each one went straig
ht forward: wherever the spirit was going they went, and turned not back.}{\insrsid8136756  13 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And in the midst of the living creatures an appearance as of burning coals of fire, as an appearance of lamps}{\insrsid8136756 
 15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And I looked, and, behold, the four one wheel on the ground near the living creatures.}{\insrsid8136756  16 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the appearance of the wheels was as the appearance of beryl: and the four had one likeness: and their work was as it were a wheel in a wheel.}{\insrsid8136756  17 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
They went on their four sides: they turned not as they went;}{\insrsid8136756  18 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 neither did their backs : and they were high: and I beheld them, and the backs of them four were full of eyes round about.}{\insrsid8136756 
 19 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And when the living creatures went, the wheels went by them: and when the living creatures lifted themselves off the earth. the wheels were lifted off.}{\insrsid8136756  20 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Wherever the cloud happened to be, there was the spirit Or, with power ready to go: the wheels went and were lifted up with them; because the spirit of life was in the wheels. 
\par }{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756 
\par }{\cs23\i\f1\fs24\insrsid8136756 Reader:}{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756  The Prokeimenon, Psalm 126, in the 4}{\cs19\f1\fs32\super\insrsid8136756 th}{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756  Tone:}{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756  
\par }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Except the Lord build the house, in vain do thy labour that build it.
\par 
\par }{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756 Stichos: }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756  Except the Lord guard the city, in vain doth he watch that guardeth her.
