\par }\pard \s17\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756 Exodus 1:1}{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
\par These are the names of the sons of Israel that came into Egypt together with Jacob their father; they came in each with their whole family.}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Ruben, Simeon, Levi, Judas,}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Issachar, Zabulon, Benjamin,}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Dan and Nephthalim, Gad and Aser.}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
But Joseph was in Egypt. And all the souls born of Jacob were seventy-five.}{\insrsid8136756  6 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And Joseph died, and all his brethren, and all that generation.}{\insrsid8136756  7 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the children of Israel increased and multiplied, and became numerous and grew exceedingly strong, and the land multiplied them.}{\insrsid8136756  8 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And there arose up another king over Egypt, who knew not Joseph.}{
\insrsid8136756  9 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he said to his nation, Behold, the race of the children of Israel is a great multitude, and is stronger than we:}{\insrsid8136756  10 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
come then, let us deal craftily with them, lest at any time they be increased, and whensoever war shall happen to us, these also shall be added to our enemies, and having prevailed against us in war, they will depart out of the land.}{\insrsid8136756  11 
}{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he set over them task-master, who should afflict them in their works; and they built strong cities for Pharao, both Pitho, and Ramesses, and On, which is Heliopolis.}{\insrsid8136756  12 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
But as they humbled them, by so much they multiplied, and grew exceedingly strong: and the Egyptians greatly abhorred the children of Israel.}{\insrsid8136756  13 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the Egyptians tyrannised over the children of Israel by force.}{\insrsid8136756  14 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And they embittered their life by hard labours, in the clay an
d in brick-making, and all the works in the plains, according to all the works, wherein they caused them to serve with violence.}{\insrsid8136756  15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the king of the Egyptians spoke to the midwives of the Hebrews; the name of the one was, Sepphora; and the name of the second, Phua.}{\insrsid8136756  16 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And he said, When ye do the office of midwives to the Hebrew women, and they are about to be delivered, if it be a male, kill it; but if a female, save it.}{\insrsid8136756  17 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
But the midwives feared God, and did not as the king of Egypt appointed them; and they saved the male children alive.}{\insrsid8136756  18 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the king of Egypt called the midwives, and said to them, Why is it that ye have done this thing, and saved the male children alive?19 And the midwives said to Pharao, The Hebrew women are not as the women of Egyp
t, for they are delivered before the midwives go in to them. So they bore children.}{\insrsid8136756  20 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And God did well to the midwives, and the people multiplied, and grew very strong. 
\par }{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756 
\par }{\cs23\i\f1\fs24\insrsid8136756 Reader:}{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756  The Prokeimenon, Psalm 128, in the 6}{\cs19\f1\fs32\super\insrsid8136756 th}{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756  Tone:}{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756  
\par }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 We have blessed you in the name of the Lord.
\par 
\par }{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756 Stichos: }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756  Many a time have they warred against me from my youth.
\par 
