\par O Lord, teach me, and I shall know: then I saw their practices.}{\insrsid8136756  19 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
But I as an innocent lamb led to the slaughter, knew not: against me they devised an evil device, saying, Come and let us put wood into his bread, and let us utterly destroy him from off the land of the living, and let his name not be remembered any more.
}{\insrsid8136756  20 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 O Lord, that judgest righteously, trying the reins and hearts, let me see thy vengeance taken upon them, for to thee I have declared my cause.}{\insrsid8136756  21 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Therefore thus saith the Lord concerning the men of Anathoth, that seek my life, that say, Thou shalt not prophesy at all in the name of the Lord, but if thou dost, thou shalt die by our hands:}{\insrsid8136756  22 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
behold, I will visit them : their young men shall die by the sword; and their sons and their daughters shall die of famine:}{\insrsid8136756  23 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
and there shall be no remnant left of them; for I will bring evil upon the dwellers in Anathoth, in the year of their visitation. 12:1 Righteous art thou, O Lord, that I may make my defence to thee, yea, I will speak to thee of judg
ments. Why is it that the way of ungodly men prospers? that all hat deal very treacherously are flourishing?}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Thou hast planted them, and they have taken root; they have begotten children, and become fruitful; thou art near to their mouth, and far from their reins.}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
But thou, Lord, knowest me; thou hast proved my heart before thee; purify them for the day of their slaughter.}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
How long shall the land mourn, and the grass of the field wither, for the wickedness of them, that dwell in it? the beasts and birds are utterly destroyed; because the people said, God shall not see our ways.}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Thy feet run, and they cause thee to faint; how wilt thou prepare to ride upon horses? and thou hast been confident in the land of thy peace? how wilt thou do in the roaring of Jordan?}{\insrsid8136756  9 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Is not my inheritance to me a hyaena's cave , or a cave round about her? Go ye, gather togetehr all the wild beasts of the field, and let them come to devour her.}{\insrsid8136756  10 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Many shepherds have destroyed my vineyard, they have defiled my portion, they have made my desirable portion a trackless wilderness;}{\insrsid8136756  11 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
it is made a complete ruin: for my sake the whole land has been utterly ruined, because there is none that lays the matter to heart.}{\insrsid8136756  14 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 For this saith the Lord, concerning all the evil neighbours th
at touch mine inheritance, which I have divided to my people Israel; Behold, I will draw them away from their land, and I will cast out Juda from the midst of them.}{\insrsid8136756  15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And it shall come to pass, after I have cast them out, that I will return, and have mercy upon them, and will cause them to dwell every one in his inheritance, and every one is his land. 
