\par And after Elius had ceased from speaking, the Lord spoke to Job through the whirlwind and clouds, saying,}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Who is this that hides counsel from me, and confines words in his heart, and thinks to conceal them from me?}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Gird thy loins like a man; and I will ask thee, and do thou answer me.}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Where wast thou when I founded the earth? tell me now, if thou hast knowledge,}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 who set the measures of it, if thou knowest? or who stretched a line upon it?}{\insrsid8136756 
 6 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 On what are its rings fastened? and who is he that laid the corner-stone upon it?}{\insrsid8136756  7 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 When the stars were made, all my angels praised me with a loud voice.}{\insrsid8136756 
 8 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And I shut up the sea with gates, when it rushed out , coming forth out its mother's womb.}{\insrsid8136756  9 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And I made a cloud its clothing, and swathed it in mist.}{\insrsid8136756  10 }
{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And I set bounds to it, surrounding it with bars and gates.}{\insrsid8136756  11 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And I said to it, Hitherto shalt thou come, but 
thou shalt not go beyond, but thy waves shall be confined within thee.}{\insrsid8136756  12 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Or did I order the morning light in thy time; and did the morning star then first see his appointed place;}{\insrsid8136756  13 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 to lay hold of the extremities of the earth, to cast out the ungodly out of it?}{\insrsid8136756  14 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Or didst thou take clay of the ground, and form a living creature, and set it with the power of speech upon the earth?}{\insrsid8136756  15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And hast thou removed light from the ungodly, and crushed the arm of the proud?}{
\insrsid8136756  16 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Or hast thou gone to the source of the sea, and walked in the tracks of the deep?}{\insrsid8136756  17 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And do the gates of death open to thee for fear; and did the porters of hell quake when they saw thee?}{\insrsid8136756  18 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And hast thou been instructed in the breadth of the whole earth under heaven? tell me now, what is the extent of it?}{\insrsid8136756  22 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 But hast thou gone to the treasures of snow? and hast thou seen the treasures of hail?
}{\insrsid8136756  23 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And is there a store of them, for thee against the time of thine enemies, for the day of wars and battle? 42:1 Then Job answered and said to the Lord,}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
I know that thou canst do all things, and nothing is impossible with thee.}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
For who is he that hides counsel from thee? or who keeps back his words, and thinks to hide them from thee? and who will tell me what I knew not, great and wonderful things which I understood not?}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
But hear me, O Lord, that I also may speak: and I will ask thee, and do thou teach me.}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 I have heard the report of thee by the ear before; but now mine eye has seen thee. 
