\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
\par Be enlightened, be enlightened, O Jerusalem, for thy light is come, and the glory of the Lord is risen upon thee.}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Behold, darkness shall cover the earth, and there shall be gross darkness on the nations: but the Lords shall appear upon thee, and his glory shall be seen upon thee.}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And kings shall walk in thy light, and nations in thy brightness.}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Lift up thine eyes round about, and behold thy children gathered: all thy sons have come from far, and thy daughters shall be borne on men's shoulders.}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Then
 shalt thou see, and fear, and be amazed in thine heart; for the wealth of the sea shall come round to thee, and of nations and peoples; and herds of camels shall come to thee,}{\insrsid8136756  6 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
and the camels of Madiam and Gaepha shall cover thee: all from Saba shall come bearing gold, and shall bring frankincense, and they shall publish the salvation of the Lord.}{\insrsid8136756  7 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And all the flocks of Kedar shall be gathered, and the rams of Nabaeoth shall come; and acceptable sacrifices shall be offered on my altar, and my house of prayer shall be glorified.}{\insrsid8136756  8 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Who are these that fly as clouds, and as doves with young ones to me?}{\insrsid8136756  9 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
The isles have waited for me, and the ships of Tharsis among the first, to bring thy children from Safar, and their silver and their gold with them, and that for the sake of the holy name of the Lord, and because the Holy One of Israel is glorified.}{
\insrsid8136756  10 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And strangers shall build thy walls, and their kings shall wait upon thee: for by reason of my wrath I smote thee, and by reason of mercy I loved thee.}{\insrsid8136756  11 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And thy gates shall be opened continually; they shall not be shut day nor night; to bring in to thee the power of the Gentiles, and their kings as captives.}{\insrsid8136756  12 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
For the nations and the kings which will not serve thee shall perish; and those nations shall be made utterly desolate.}{\insrsid8136756  13 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the glory of Libanus shall come to thee, with the cypress, and pine, and cedar together, to glorify my holy place.}{\insrsid8136756  14 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And the sons of them that afflicted thee, and of them that provoked thee, shall come to thee in fear ; and thou shalt be called Sion, the city of the Holy One of Israel.}{\insrsid8136756  15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Because thou has become desolate and hated, and there was no helper, therefore I will make thee a perpetual gladness, a joy of many generations.}{\insrsid8136756  16 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And thou shalt suck the milk of the Gentiles, and shalt eat the wealth of kings: and shalt know that I am the Lord that saves thee and delivers thee, the Holy One of Israel. 
