\par And a day came, when Elisaie passed over to Soman, and there was a great lady there, and she constrained him to eat bread: and it came to pass as often as he went into the city, that he turned aside to eat there.}{\insrsid8136756  9 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the woman said to her husband, See now, I know that this is a holy man of God who comes over continually to us.}{\insrsid8136756  10 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Let us now make for him an upper chamber, a small place; and let us put there for him a bed, and a table, and a stool, and a candlestick: and it shall come to pass that when he comes in to us, he shall turn in thither.}{\insrsid8136756  11 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And a day came, and he went in thither, and turned aside into the upper chamber, and lay there.}{\insrsid8136756  12 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he said to Giezi his servant, Call me this Somanite. an
d he called her, and she stood before him.}{\insrsid8136756  13 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And he said to him, Say now to her, Behold, thou hast taken all this trouble for us; what should I do for thee? Hast thou any request to make to the king, or to the captain of the host? And she said, I dwell in the midst of my people.}{\insrsid8136756 
 14 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he said to Giezi, What must we do for her? and Giezi his servant said, Indeed she has no son, and her husband is old.}{\insrsid8136756  15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he called her, and she stood by the door.}
{\insrsid8136756  16 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And Elisaie said to her, At this time next year, as the season is, thou shalt be alive, and embrace a son. And she said, Nay, my lord, do not lie to thy servant.}{\insrsid8136756  17 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the woman conceived, and bore a son at the very time, as the season was, being alive, as Elisaie said to her.}{\insrsid8136756  18 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the child grew: and it c
ame to pass when he went out to his father to the reapers,}{\insrsid8136756  19 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 that he said to his father, My head, my head. and his father said to a servant, carry him to his mother.}{\insrsid8136756  20 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he carried him to his mother, and he lay upon her knees till noon, and died.}{\insrsid8136756  21 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 An
d she carried him up and laid him on the bed of the man of god; and she shut the door upon him, and went out.}{\insrsid8136756  22 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And she called her husband, and said, Send now for me one of the young men, and one of the asses, and I will ride quickly to the man of God, and return.}{\insrsid8136756  23 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And he said, Why art thou going to him to-day? It is neither new moon, nor the Sabbath. And she said, It is well.}{\insrsid8136756  24 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And she saddled the ass, and said to her servant, Be quick, proceed: spare not on my account to ride, unless I shall tell thee. Go, and thou shalt proceed, and come to the man of God to mount Carmel.}{\insrsid8136756  25 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And she rode and came to the man of God to the mountain: and it came to pass when Elisaie saw her coming, that he said to Giezi his servant, See now, that Somanite comes.}{\insrsid8136756  26 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Now r
un to meet her, and thou shalt say, Is it well with thee? is it well with thy husband? is it well with the child? and she said, It is well.}{\insrsid8136756  27 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And she came to Elisaie to the mountain, and laid hold of his feet; and Giezi drew near to thrust her away. And Elisaie said, Let her alone, for her soul is much grieved in her, and the Lord has hidden it from me, and has not told it me.}{\insrsid8136756 
 28 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And she said, Did I ask a son of my lord? For did I not say, Do not deal deceitfully with me?}{\insrsid8136756  29 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And Elisaie said to Giezi, Gird
 up thy loins, and take my staff in thy hand, and go: if thou meet any man, thou shalt not salute him, and if a man salute thee thou shalt not answer him: and thou shalt lay my staff on the child's face.}{\insrsid8136756  30 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the mother of the child said, As the Lord lives and as thy soul lives, I will not leave thee. And Elisaie arose, and went after her.}{\insrsid8136756  31 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And Giezi went on before her, and laid his staff on the child's face: but there was neither voice nor any hearing. So he returned to meet him, and told him, saying, The child is not awaked.}{\insrsid8136756  32 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And Elisaie went into the house, and, behold, the dead child was laid upon his bed.}{\insrsid8136756  33 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And Elisaie went into the house, and shut the door upon themselves, the two, and prayed to the Lord.}{\insrsid8136756 
 34 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he went up, and lay upon the child, and put his mouth upon his mouth, and his eyes upon his eyes, and his hands upon his hands; and bowed himself upon him, and the flesh of the child grew warm.}{\insrsid8136756  35 }
{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he returned and walked up and down in the house: and he went up, and bowed himself on the child seven times; and the child opened his eyes.}{\insrsid8136756  36 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And Elisaie cried out to Giezi, and said, Call this Somanite. So he called her, and she came in to him: and Elisaie said, Take thy son.}{\insrsid8136756  37 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the woman went in, and fell at his feet, and did obeisance
 bowing to the ground; and she took her son, and went out. 
