\par Then he remembered the ancient of days, saying, Where is he that brought up from the sea the shepherd of the sheep? where is he that put his Holy Spirit in them?}{\insrsid8136756  12 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
who led Moses with his right hand, the arm of his glory? he forced the water to separate from before him to make himself an everlasting name.}{\insrsid8136756  13 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
He led them through the deep, as a horse through the wilderness, and they fainted not,}{\insrsid8136756  14 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 and as cattle through a plain: the Spirit came down from the Lord and guided them: thus thou leddest thy people,
 to make thyself a glorious name.}{\insrsid8136756  15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Turn from heaven, and look from thy holy habitation and from thy glory: where is thy zeal and thy strength? where is the abundance of thy mercy and of thy compassions, that thou hast withholden thyself from us?}{\insrsid8136756  16 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 For thou art our Father; for through Abraham knew us not, and Israel did not acknowledge us, yet do thou, O Lord, our Father, deliver us: thy name has been upon us from the beginning.}{\insrsid8136756  17 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Why hast thou caused us to err, O Lord, from thy way? and has hardened our hearts, that we should not fear thee? Return for thy servants' sake, for the sake of the tribes of thine inheritance,}{\insrsid8136756  18 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 that we may inherit a small part of thy holy mountain. We are become as at the beginning , when thou didst not rule over us, and thy n
ame was not called upon us. 64:1 If thou wouldest open the heaven, trembling will take hold upon the mountains from thee, and they shall melt,}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
as wax melts before the fire; and fire shall burn up the enemies, and thy name shall be manifest among the adversaries: at thy presence the nations shall be troubled,}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
whenever thou shalt work gloriously; trembling from thee shall take hold upon the mountains.}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 From of old we have not heard, neither have our eyes seen a God beside thee, and thy works which thou w
ilt perform to them that wait for mercy.}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
For these blessings shall happen to them that work righteousness, and they shall remember thy ways: behold, thou wast angry and we have sinned; therefore we have erred. 
