\par }\pard \s17\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8136756 Daniel 3:1}{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
\par In his eighteenth year Nabuchodonosor the king made a golden image, its height was sixty cubits, its breadth six cubits: and he set it up in the plain of Deira, in the province of Babylon.}{\insrsid8136756  2 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And he sent forth to gather the governors, and the captains, and the heads of provinces, chiefs, and princes, and those who were in authority, and all the rulers of districts, to come to the dedication of the image.}{\insrsid8136756  3 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 So the heads of provinces, the governors, the captains, the chiefs, the great princes, those who were i
n authority, and all the rulers of districts, were gathered to the dedication of the image which king Nabuchodonosor had set up; and they stood before the image.}{\insrsid8136756  4 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Then a herald cried aloud, To you it is commanded, ye peoples, tribes, and languages,}{\insrsid8136756  5 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 at w
hat hour ye shall hear the sound of the trumpet, and pipe, and harp, and sackbut, and psaltery , and every king of music, ye shall fall down and worship the golden image which king Nabuchodonosor has set up.}{\insrsid8136756  6 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And whosoever shall not fall down and worship, in the same hour he shall be cast into the burning fiery furnace.}{\insrsid8136756  7 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And it came to pass when the nations heard the sound of the trumpet, and pipe, and harp, and sackbut, and psaltery, and all kinds of music, all the nations, tribes, and languages, fell do
wn and worshipped the golden image which king Nabuchodonosor had set up.}{\insrsid8136756  8 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Then came near certain Chaldeans, and accused the Jews to the king, saying,}{\insrsid8136756  9 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
O king, live for ever.}{\insrsid8136756  10 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Thou, O king, has made a decree that every man who shall hear the sound of the trumpet, and pipe, and harp, sackbut, and psaltery, and all kinds of music,}{\insrsid8136756  11 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 and shall not fall down and worship the golden image, shall be cast into the burning fiery furnace.}{\insrsid8136756  12 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 There are certain Jews whom thou has appointed over the affairs of the p
rovince of Babylon, Sedrach, Misach, and Abdenago, who have not obeyed thy decree, O king: they serve not thy gods, and worship not the golden image which thou hast set up.}{\insrsid8136756  13 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Then Nabuchodonosor in wrath and anger commanded to bring Sedrach, Misach, and Abdenago: and they were brought before the king.}{\insrsid8136756  14 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And Nabuchodonosor answered and said to them, Is it true, Sedrach, Misach, and Abdenago, that ye serve not my gods, and worship not the golden image which I have set up?}{\insrsid8136756  15 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Now then if ye be ready, whensoe
ver ye shall hear the sound of the trumpet, and pipe, and harp, and sackbut, and psaltery, and harmony, and every kind of music, to fall down and worship the golden image which I have made; well: but if ye worship not, in the same hour ye shall be cast in
to the burning fiery furnace; and who is the God that shall deliver you out of my hand?}{\insrsid8136756  16 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Then answered Sedrach, Misach and Abdenago and said to king Nabuchodonosor, We have no need to answer thee concerning this matter. For our God whom we serve is in the
 heavens, able to deliver us from the burning fiery furnace, and he will rescue us from thy hands, O king.}{\insrsid8136756  18 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
But if not, be it known to thee, O king, that we will not serve thy gods, nor worship the image which thou hast set up.}{\insrsid8136756  19 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Then Nabuchodonosor was
 filled with wrath, and the form of his countenance was changed toward Sedrach, Misach, and Abdenago: and he gave orders to heat the furnace seven times more than usual, until it should burn to the uttermost.}{\insrsid8136756  20 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And he commanded mighty men to bind Sedrach, Misach, and Abdenago, and to cast them into the burning fiery furnace.}{\insrsid8136756  21 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Then those men were bound with their coats , and caps, and hose, and were cast into the midst of the burning fiery furnace,}{\insrsid8136756  22 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 forasmuch as the king's word prevailed; and the furnace was made exceeding hot.
}{\insrsid8136756  23 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Then these three men, Sedrach, Misach, and Abdenago, fell bound into the midst of the burning furnace, and walked in the midst of the flame, singing praise to God, and blessing the Lord.}{
\insrsid8136756  24 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Then Azariah stood and offered this prayer; in the midst of the fire he opened his mouth and said:}{\insrsid8136756  25 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
"Blessed art Thou, O Lord, God of our fathers, and worthy of praise; and Thy name is glorified for ever.}{\insrsid8136756  26 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 For Thou art just in all that Thou hast done to us, and all Thy works are true and 
Thy ways right, and all Thy judgements are truth.}{\insrsid8136756  27 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Thou hast executed true judgements in all that Thou hast brought upon us and upon Jerusalem, the holy city of our fathers, for in truth and justice Thou hast brought all this upon us because of our sins.}{\insrsid8136756  28 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 For we have sinfully and lawlessly departed from Thee, and have sinned in all things and have not obeyed Thy commandments; we have not observed them or done them, as Thou hast commanded us that it might go well with us.}{
\insrsid8136756  29 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 So all that Thou hast brought upon us, and all that Thou hast done to us, Thou hast done in true judgement.}{\insrsid8136756  30 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Thou hast given us into the hands of lawless enemies, most hateful rebels, and to an unjust king, the most wicked in all the world.}{\insrsid8136756  31 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And now we cannot open our mouths; sham
e and disgrace have befallen Thy servants and worshippers.}{\insrsid8136756  32 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
For Thy name's sake do not give us up utterly, and do not break Thy covenant, and do not withdraw Thy mercy from us, for the sake of Abraham Thy beloved and for the sake of Isaac Thy servant and
 Israel Thy holy one, to whom Thou didst promise to make their descendants as amny as the stars of heaven and as the sand on the shore of the sea.}{\insrsid8136756  33 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
For we, O Lord, have become fewer than any nation, and are brought low this day in all the world because of our sins.}{\insrsid8136756  34 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
And at this time there is no prince, or prophet, or leader, no burnt offering, or sacrifice, or oblation, or incense, no place to make an offering before Thee or to find mercy.}{\insrsid8136756  35 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Yet with a contrite heart and a humble spirit may we be accep
ted, as though it were with burnt offerings of rams and bulls, and with tens of thousands of fat lambs; such may our sacrifice be in Thy sight this day, and may we wholly follow Thee, for there will be no shame for those who trust in Thee.}{
\insrsid8136756  36 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And now with all our heart we follow Thee, we fear Thee and seek Thy face.}{\insrsid8136756  37 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Do not put us to shame, but deal with us in Thy forbearance and in Thy abundant mercy.}{\insrsid8136756  38 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Deliver us in accordance with Thy marvelous works, and give glory to Thy name, O Lord!}{\insrsid8136756  39 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Let all who do harm to Thy servants be put to shame; let them be disgraced and deprived of all power and dominion, and let their strengths be broken.}{\insrsid8136756  40 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Let them know that Thou art the Lord, the only God, glorious over the whole world."}{\insrsid8136756  41 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Now the king's servants who threw them in did not cease feeding the furnace fires with naptha, pitch, tow, and brush.}{
\insrsid8136756  42 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And the flame streamed out above the furnace forty nine cubits, and it broke through and burned those of the Chaldeans whom it caught about in the furnace.}{\insrsid8136756  43 }{
\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 But
 the angel of the Lord came down into the furnace to be with Azariah and his companions, and drove the fiery flame out of the furnace, and made the midst of the furnace like a moist whistling wind, so that the fire did not touch them at all or hurt or tro
uble them.}{\insrsid8136756  44 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Then the three, as with one mouth, praised and glorified and blessed God in the furnace, saying:}{\insrsid8136756  45 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
"Blessed art Thou, O Lord, God of our fathers, and to be praised and highly exalted for ever;}{\insrsid8136756  46 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 And blessed is Thy glorious, holy name, and to be highly praised and highly exalted for ever;}{
\insrsid8136756  47 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Blessed art Thou in the temple of Thy holy glory, and to be extolled and highly glorified for ever.}{\insrsid8136756  48 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Blessed art Thou, who sittest upon cherubim and lookest upon the deeps, and to be praised and highly exalted for ever.}{\insrsid8136756  49 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 
Blessed art Thou upon the throne of Thy kingdom, and to be extolled and highly exalted for ever.}{\insrsid8136756  50 }{\cs19\f1\fs32\insrsid8136756 Blessed art Thou in the firmament of heaven, and to be sung and glorified for ever. 
